# Project Structure & File Organization

## Component Organization
- Store ALL components in `/components` directory
- Follow sub-folder structure based on feature/page groupings
- Use descriptive folder names that match the application structure

## Folder Structure Examples
```
/components/
  ├── dashboard/
  │   ├── home/           # Homepage components
  │   ├── settings/       # Settings page components
  │   └── profile/        # Profile page components
  ├── chat/
  │   ├── message/        # Message-related components
  │   ├── sidebar/        # Chat sidebar components
  │   └── input/          # Chat input components
  ├── ui/                 # Reusable UI components (shadcn)
  └── layout/             # Layout components
```

## Other Directory Rules
- `/lib/types/` - All TypeScript type definitions
- `/server/actions/` - Server actions code
- `/lib/utils/` - Utility functions
- `/lib/hooks/` - Custom React hooks

## File Naming
- Use PascalCase for component files: `ChatMessage.tsx`
- Use camelCase for utility files: `formatDate.ts`
- Use kebab-case for page files: `chat-page.tsx`
